## 🔍 Key Research Finding

This result is intentionally included as a **negative result** — and negative results matter in research.

The MA50/200 Golden Cross, widely used in equity markets, **significantly underperforms on EUR/USD Forex**. This failure reveals a core insight:

> *Trend-following strategies optimized for equity markets do not directly transfer to Forex markets, which exhibit stronger mean-reverting behavior.*

**Comparison across all three strategies in this series:**

| Strategy | Total Return | Sharpe | Max Drawdown |
|---|---|---|---|
| RSI Mean Reversion | +6.53% | 0.55 | -2.28% |
| EMA + RSI Combo | +11.11% | 0.42 | -8.68% |
| MA Crossover | -20.33% | -1.15 | -22.36% |

**Takeaway:** Mean reversion approaches (RSI-based) outperform trend-following (MA crossover) on EUR/USD — suggesting EUR/USD exhibits statistically significant mean-reverting price behavior over this period.

